---
description: Agent security rules for setup, shell commands, and secrets handling
alwaysApply: true
---

The canonical security rules live in `docs/SECURITY.md`. Read and follow them before any install/setup command, shell execution, or work that touches secrets or credentials.

Hard lines (full detail in `docs/SECURITY.md`):

- No remote pipe-to-shell (`curl | bash` and equivalents); no unreviewed remote or obfuscated scripts.
- No destructive commands (`rm -rf`, `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fdx`, database drops, mass deletes) without explicit user approval; no `sudo` unless the user asks.
- Never print, commit, or expose secret values (`.env` contents, API keys, tokens, service-role keys); describe presence only.
- Prefer `npm ci` when `package-lock.json` exists; no override install flags without approval.
